STDERR 709
tests/error_cannot_mix_typed_variadic_sources.glos:8:9: ERROR: Cannot supply variadics from two sources. This argument starts a variadic source...
tests/error_cannot_mix_typed_variadic_sources.glos:8:13: ... But this spread here starts another

NOTE: Variadic arguments must originate from a single variadic source. Explicit variadic arguments are
lowered into a temporary stack array with a compile time known length, while a spread slice is passed
directly as it is, the difference being that its length is not known at compile time. Mixing these two
is not supported, since that would require the combination of a compile time length and a runtime length
into a compile time length, which is not possible.

